        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 9 at 6:15PM MDT until September 9 at 7:30PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>SVRGLD

The National Weather Service in Goodland has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
North central Yuma County in northeastern Colorado...

* Until 730 PM MDT.

* At 615 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Highland
Center, or 16 miles west of Holyoke, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
north central Yuma County, including the following locations...
Clarkville.

This includes Highway 385 between mile markers 262 and 270.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
